At one point I was begging and crying for someone to let me stay and they still turned me away. I could have so easily become another statistic, another story last night.

I do feel guilty for putting myself in that situation but the takeaway shouldn’t be that I shouldn’t let go once in a while out of fear. But last night proved to me that women’s safety isn’t taken seriously or prioritised.

I’m so thankful that I was able to find somewhere that sat me down, gave me a glass of water and a charging port for my phone and had a someone stay with me till I’d ordered a taxi and then checked I had gotten in the right one.

Without even a word of help or advise really scares me about this countries attitudes towards women and women in need. After last night I’m not at all surprised at the number of women who go missing, wind up dead, are abducted etc on a daily basis

Were it not for the 5th place I tried who helped me get home ,I could have so easily been taken advantage of and or hurt. Yes I’m aware that I put myself in a dangerous place by having a drink and what Covid regulations can mean but to be turned away so many times
Keep in mind I was clearly vulnerable, alone and not demanding anything other than help. 4 different groups of people turned me away with not even a suggestion of what I could do or where I could go.

I went into a nearby restaurant to ask if they would charge my phone and let me stay there until I had an Uber or if they could call one for me.  
I got told no and asked to leave at 4 SEPARATE establishments.
